   Licensed under the Open Database License (ODbL) v1.0.
   Full text: https://opendatacommons.org/licenses/odbl/1-0/

   You are free to share, create from, and adapt this database, provided you:
   - Attribute: credit "MechanicDB" and link to this repository;
   - Share-Alike: distribute adapted databases under ODbL v1.0;
   - Keep open: do not apply technical measures that restrict reuse of
     redistributed copies.

   Commercial applications requiring the full database (15,886 codes) or
   rights beyond ODbL terms require a separate commercial license —
   self-serve at https://mechanicdb-public.pages.dev/ or email
   mechanicdb.urologist336@simplelogin.com for inquiries.

2. UPSTREAM ATTRIBUTION (code definitions)

   DTC code definitions are compiled from a public, MIT-licensed
   compilation of SAE J2012-derived trouble codes. The upstream MIT license
   and copyright notice are preserved in LICENSE-upstream.txt, as required.

